##Form View

A form may contain different kinds of attributes and is up to the platform to decide which one is the most suitable representation depending on the data type and edit mode of the attribute.

For instance geographical coordinate attribute may be displayed using a map in the cell (like in home claims), an integer or float can be displayed using an stepper to increase decrease the value, a date or a string may be displayed as a picker or a single line field depending on the attribute edit mode. 

###iOS classes: ObjectEditorVC | ObjectEditorDM

###[acm/execute/pack](http://schemas.isis-papyrus.com/acm/execute/pack) ([agnostic/form](http://schemas.isis-papyrus.com/agnostic/form)) | autosave-form

###[acm/execute/pack](http://schemas.isis-papyrus.com/acm/execute/pack) ([agnostic/form](http://schemas.isis-papyrus.com/agnostic/form)) | document-builder

###[acm/execute/pack](http://schemas.isis-papyrus.com/acm/execute/pack)([agnostic/form](http://schemas.isis-papyrus.com/agnostic/form)) | default

###[acm/execute/pack](http://schemas.isis-papyrus.com/acm/execute/pack) ([agnostic/form](http://schemas.isis-papyrus.com/agnostic/form)) | form

![](Screenshots/iPhone/AgnosticForm/form.png)

---

